article.headline: Petraitis' 20 lead Air Force over Portland 80-58

images.name: Air Force Falcons vs. Portland Pilots: Full Highlights
images.caption: Air Force Falcons vs. Portland Pilots: Full Highlights

article.linkText: Petraitis' 20 lead Air Force over Portland 80-58
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- — Rytis Petraitis' 20 points helped Air Force defeat Portland 80-58 on Sunday night. Petraitis added five rebounds and three steals for the Falcons (7-2). Ethan Taylor was 6 of 10 shooting (4 for 6 from 3-point range) to add 16 points. Kellan Boylan was 5 of 10 shooting, including 2 for 5 from 3-point range, and went 3 for 3 from the line to finish with 15 points, while adding six rebounds and five steals. The Falcons extended their winning streak to six games. Chris Austin led the Pilots (5-4) in scoring, finishing with 15 points and two steals. Tyler Robertson added 14 points and five assists for Portland. In addition, Vukasin Masic had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
